article.headline: Oral Roberts 82, John Brown 58
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Robert Jarvis scored 25 points as he fueled a comeback from an early deficit to lead Oral Roberts past John Brown 82-58 on Monday night. Jarvis was 10-of-17 from the field, including 3-of-7 on 3-pointers, and had five assists. He scored 13 points in the first half to help ORU erase John Brown's 17-7 lead and take a 37-28 lead at intermission. Andrius Mikutis led John Brown's Golden Eagles (6-1), of the NAIA, with 12 points. Oral Roberts scored the first eight points of the second half to take a 45-28 lead and John Brown never got closer than 13 points the rest of the game.
